<p class="ko" style="font-size:12px;color:#52525b;margin-top:24px">출처: Seligman, M.E.P. &amp; Maier, S.F. (1967), "Failure to Escape Traumatic Shock," Journal of Experimental Psychology, 74(1), 1–9. Denrell, J. (2007), "Adaptive Learning and Risk Taking," Psychological Review, 114(1), 177–187. Seru, A., Shumway, T., &amp; Stoffman, N. (2010), "Learning by Trading," Review of Financial Studies, 23(2), 705–739. Thaler, R.H. &amp; Benartzi, S. (2004), "Save More Tomorrow: Using Behavioral Economics to Increase Employee Saving," Journal of Political Economy, 112(S1), S164–S187. 연속 실패 구간(run) 확률은 승률 55%를 가정한 이항분포에 기반해 필자가 직접 계산.</p>
<p class="en" style="font-size:12px;color:#52525b;margin-top:24px">Sources: Seligman, M.E.P. &amp; Maier, S.F. (1967), "Failure to Escape Traumatic Shock," Journal of Experimental Psychology, 74(1), 1–9. Denrell, J. (2007), "Adaptive Learning and Risk Taking," Psychological Review, 114(1), 177–187. Seru, A., Shumway, T., &amp; Stoffman, N. (2010), "Learning by Trading," Review of Financial Studies, 23(2), 705–739. Thaler, R.H. &amp; Benartzi, S. (2004), "Save More Tomorrow: Using Behavioral Economics to Increase Employee Saving," Journal of Political Economy, 112(S1), S164–S187. Losing-streak run probabilities calculated by the author under the binomial distribution assuming a 55% win rate.</p>
<p class="ja" style="font-size:12px;color:#52525b;margin-top:24px">出典: Seligman, M.E.P. &amp; Maier, S.F. (1967), "Failure to Escape Traumatic Shock," Journal of Experimental Psychology, 74(1), 1–9。Denrell, J. (2007), "Adaptive Learning and Risk Taking," Psychological Review, 114(1), 177–187。Seru, A., Shumway, T., &amp; Stoffman, N. (2010), "Learning by Trading," Review of Financial Studies, 23(2), 705–739。Thaler, R.H. &amp; Benartzi, S. (2004), "Save More Tomorrow: Using Behavioral Economics to Increase Employee Saving," Journal of Political Economy, 112(S1), S164–S187。連敗区間(ラン)の確率は勝率55%を仮定した二項分布に基づき筆者が独自に計算。</p>
