<p class="it" style="font-size:12px;color:#52525b;margin-top:24px">Fonti: Seligman, M.E.P. &amp; Maier, S.F. (1967), "Failure to Escape Traumatic Shock," Journal of Experimental Psychology, 74(1), 1–9. Denrell, J. (2007), "Adaptive Learning and Risk Taking," Psychological Review, 114(1), 177–187. Seru, A., Shumway, T., &amp; Stoffman, N. (2010), "Learning by Trading," Review of Financial Studies, 23(2), 705–739. Thaler, R.H. &amp; Benartzi, S. (2004), "Save More Tomorrow: Using Behavioral Economics to Increase Employee Saving," Journal of Political Economy, 112(S1), S164–S187. Probabilità delle serie di perdite calcolate dall'autore secondo la distribuzione binomiale assumendo un tasso di successo del 55%.</p>
